<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8" standalone="yes"?><rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom"><channel><title>VCF Operations 9.0 on My Cloudy World</title><link>http://jadenetworksolutions.co.uk/categories/vcf-operations-9.0/</link><description>Recent content in VCF Operations 9.0 on My Cloudy World</description><generator>Hugo -- gohugo.io</generator><language>en</language><managingEditor>gblake@jadenetworks.co.uk (Gary Blake)</managingEditor><webMaster>gblake@jadenetworks.co.uk (Gary Blake)</webMaster><copyright>Copyright © 2019–2026, Gary Blake; all rights reserved.</copyright><lastBuildDate>Thu, 10 Jul 2025 00:00:00 +0000</lastBuildDate><atom:link href="http://jadenetworksolutions.co.uk/categories/vcf-operations-9.0/index.xml" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml"/><item><title>Using VMware.Sdk.Vcf.Ops: Commands for VCF Operations</title><link>http://jadenetworksolutions.co.uk/post/vcf-90/vcf-90-powercli-operations-cmdlets/</link><pubDate>Thu, 10 Jul 2025 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><author>gblake@jadenetworks.co.uk (Gary Blake)</author><guid>http://jadenetworksolutions.co.uk/post/vcf-90/vcf-90-powercli-operations-cmdlets/</guid><description><p>VCF PowerCLI 9.0 now includes a module called<code>VMware.Sdk.Vcf.Ops</code>, this modules contains auto-generated cmdlets to support VCF Operations Public APIs. Use can use this post as a quick reference guide.</p><h3 id="connecting-to-a-vcf-operations-instance-with-local-credentials">Connecting to a VCF Operations Instance with Local Credentials</h3><ol><li><p>Start a PowerShell session.</p></li><li><p>Connect to a VCF Operations instance using local credentials by running the following command:</p></li></ol><div class="highlight"><pre tabindex="0" class="chroma"><code class="language-powershell" data-lang="powershell"><span class="line"><span class="ln">1</span><span class="cl"><span class="nb">Connect-VcfOpsServer</span><span class="n">-Server</span><span class="nb">flt-ops01a</span><span class="p">.</span><span class="py">rainpole</span><span class="p">.</span><span class="py">io</span><span class="n">-User</span><span class="n">admin</span><span class="n">-Password</span><span class="n">VMw</span><span class="nv">@re1</span><span class="p">!</span><span class="n">VMw</span><span class="nv">@re1</span><span class="p">!</span></span></span></code></pre></div><ol start="3"><li>Once connected the following information is stored in<code>$defaultOpsConnections</code>.</li></ol><div class="highlight"><pre tabindex="0" class="chroma"><code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash"><span class="line"><span class="ln"> 1</span><span class="cl">ServiceUri : https://flt-ops01a.rainpole.io/</span></span><span class="line"><span class="ln"> 2</span><span class="cl">SessionSecret : 54aa4efb-3acd-4a14-ad75-10e66742a96d::c38a1c14-0ea4-4f3f-abe8-40afc55bae6d</span></span><span class="line"><span class="ln"> 3</span><span class="cl">User : admin</span></span><span class="line"><span class="ln"> 4</span><span class="cl">IsConnected : True</span></span><span class="line"><span class="ln"> 5</span><span class="cl">Id : /VcfOpsServer<span class="o">=</span>admin@flt-ops01a.rainpole.io:443/</span></span><span class="line"><span class="ln"> 6</span><span class="cl">Name : flt-ops01a.rainpole.io</span></span><span class="line"><span class="ln"> 7</span><span class="cl">Uid : /VcfOpsServer<span class="o">=</span>admin@flt-ops01a.rainpole.io:443/</span></span><span class="line"><span class="ln"> 8</span><span class="cl">ProductVersion : VCF Operations 9.0.0.0</span></span><span class="line"><span class="ln"> 9</span><span class="cl">ServerUri : https://flt-ops01a.rainpole.io/</span></span><span class="line"><span class="ln">10</span><span class="cl">UUID : /VcfOpsServer<span class="o">=</span>admin@flt-ops01a.rainpole.io:443/</span></span><span class="line"><span class="ln">11</span><span class="cl">Port :<span class="m">443</span></span></span></code></pre></div><ol start="4"><li>Disconnect from a VCF Operations instance by running the following command:</li></ol><div class="highlight"><pre tabindex="0" class="chroma"><code class="language-powershell" data-lang="powershell"><span class="line"><span class="ln">1</span><span class="cl"><span class="nb">Disconnect-VcfOpsServer</span><span class="n">-Server</span><span class="nb">flt-ops01a</span><span class="p">.</span><span class="py">rainpole</span><span class="p">.</span><span class="py">io</span></span></span></code></pre></div><h3 id="display-all-vcf-operations-get-command-details">Display All VCF Operations GET Command Details</h3><ol><li><p>Start a PowerShell session.</p></description></item></channel></rss>